'''Nomi Shrine''' (のみじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Imaise-chō|Q11376737|WD=Q11376737|1=Imaise}}, {{ill|lt=Ichinomiya|Q270810|WD=Q270810|1=Ichinomiya, Aichi}}, {{ill|lt=Aichi Prefecture|Q80434|WD=Q80434|1=Aichi Prefecture}}. It is identified with “Nomi Shrine” of Nakashima District, {{ill|lt=Owari Province|Q514506|WD=Q514506|1=Owari Province}}, in the {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|WD=Q11064932|lt=shikinaisha list|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}<ref>There is also a theory identifying it with {{ill|lt=Asai Shrine (Inazawa)|UNKNOWN|lt=Asai Shrine}} in Asai, {{ill|lt=Inazawa|Q389562|WD=Q389562|1=Inazawa}} (e.g., Amano Nobukage’s ''Hongoku Jinmyōchō Shūsetsu'', Matsudaira Kunizan’s ''{{ill|lt=Chōshū Fushi|Q137847623|WD=Q137847623|1=Chōshūfushi}}'' ({{ill|lt=1752|Q6679|WD=Q6679|1=1492}}), and ''{{ill|lt=Owari Meisho Zue Kōhen|UNKNOWN|lt=Owari Meisho Zue, latter volume}}'' ({{ill|lt=1842|Q6754|WD=Q6754|1=Charm quark}})).</ref>. Its former rank under the {{ill|lt=Modern shrine ranking system|Q712534|WD=Q712534|1=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines}} was {{ill|lt=village shrine|Q134917284|WD=Q134917284|1=Son-sha}}.

=== Enshrined deities ===
* {{ill|lt=Nomi no Sukune|Q965742|WD=Q965742|lt=Nomi no Sukune-no-Mikoto|1=Nomi no Sukune}}
* {{ill|WD=Q10940685|lt=Ame-no-Hohi|Q10940685|WD=Q10940685|WD=Q10940685|lt=Ame-no-Hohi-no-Mikoto|1=Ame no Hohi}}
* {{ill|lt=Amaterasu|Q455602|WD=Q455602|lt=Amaterasu-Ōmikami|1=Amaterasu}}
These three {{ill|lt=pillars (deities)|Q16283888|WD=Q16283888|lt=deities|1=deities}} are the main deities; {{ill|WD=Q3080728|lt=Ukanomitama|Q3080728|WD=Q3080728|lt=Uka-no-Mitama-no-Mikoto|1=Ukanomitama}} and {{ill|lt=Susanoo|Q272993|WD=Q272993|lt=Susa-no-O-no-Mikoto|1=Susanoo-no-Mikoto}} are additionally enshrined.

From the shrine name “Nomi,” the common view is that the deity is either Nomi no Sukune-no-Mikoto (ancestral deity of the {{ill|lt=Haji clan|Q10927758|WD=Q10927758|1=Haji clan}}) or Ame-no-Hohi-no-Mikoto. In the precinct is the '''Nomi Shrine Kofun''', part of the {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Imaise Kofun group|1=UNKNOWN}}, where {{ill|lt=magatama|Q334232|WD=Q334232|1=Magatama}} and {{ill|lt=haniwa|Q849376|WD=Q849376|1=Haniwa}} have been unearthed. This also supports that the Haji clan was deeply involved not only in producing {{ill|lt=pottery|Q1377111|WD=Q1377111|1=Earthenware}} but also in building {{ill|lt=kofun|Q1141225|WD=Q1141225|1=Kofun}}.

=== History ===
Its founding date is unknown, but it is presumed to have been established when the Haji clan developed this region. In the {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|WD=Q11064932|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}} it is listed as a {{ill|lt=kokuhei shōsha|UNKNOWN|lt=kokuhei small shrine}}, and in the ''Owari-koku Jinmyōchō'' it is recorded as “Junior Third Rank, Nomi Tenjin.” In the 6th year of {{ill|lt=Ōei|Q1193078|WD=Q1193078|1=Ōei}} ({{ill|lt=1399|Q6422|WD=Q6422|1=1399}}), the “Owari Province kokuga unpaid-tax report” (in the ''{{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Daigoji documents|1=UNKNOWN}}'') mentions “Nomi-sha,” leading to the view that it held {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=shrine lands|1=UNKNOWN}} within the {{ill|lt=kokuga domain|Q11421344|WD=Q11421344|lt=kokuga territory|1=Kokugaryō}} at the time<ref name="一宮市史">''Newly Compiled History of Ichinomiya City, Main Text Upper Volume'', Ichinomiya City, 1977.</ref>. There is also a theory that the district name “Miyaushiro” means a settlement north of this shrine (Tsuda Masao, ''Study of Owari Place Names'').

=== Cultural properties ===
* {{ill|lt=Castanopsis sieboldii|Q846994|WD=Q846994|1=Castanopsis sieboldii}} - Trunk circumference 2.5 m and height 20 m; a rare giant of its species with vigorous growth, designated a {{ill|lt=natural monument|Q23790|WD=Q23790|1=Natural monument}} of Ichinomiya.
*Nomi Shrine Kofun - A small {{ill|lt=round tumulus|Q11394747|WD=Q11394747|1=Round Kofun}} about 20 m long and 1 m high, thought to date to early period III of the {{ill|lt=Kofun period|Q459939|WD=Q459939|1=Kofun period}} (first half of the 5th century)<ref name="一宮市史"/>. The Imaise Kofun group containing this tumulus is designated a city {{ill|lt=historic site|Q1081138|WD=Q1081138|1=Historic site}}.

=== Access ===
*15 minutes on foot from {{ill|lt=Imaise Station|Q6002985|WD=Q6002985|1=Imaise Station}} on the {{ill|lt=Nagoya Main Line|Q1137838|WD=Q1137838|1=Meitetsu Nagoya Main Line}} of {{ill|lt=Nagoya Railroad|Q30850|WD=Q30850|1=Meitetsu}}

